body:
I recently received a warning from Riot, &#039;warning&#039; me about my use of the third-party League of Legends Add-on thingy (called MK Jogo)... Now the application literally only grants the user an alternative cursor to replace the outdated league cursor, offline skins (skins from the game that only show up for the user), a quick message option (which sucks because it lags the game), a jungle timer which is pretty much the same as the one in game right now and some in-game recording thing... so I want to know if I should take the warning seriously or legit completely stop using the application??? P.S (just going to quote what the email said) &quot;For now, this is a warning, but continued use of the program will result in suspension placed against you, and may ultimately result in permanent account closure&quot;

Additionally, the email also said, &quot;this application automates several actions on your behalf, including chat and jungle timers.&quot; now I&#039;d like to add that in order to use the quick message you have to &quot;Ctrl+T&quot; followed by a number to select a message which isn&#039;t automated, not to mention character restriction, as it only allows 20 characters to your message at which point you realize that you just wasted 4 seconds trying to use the &quot;automated&quot; action. Now the jungle timer requires u to physically see the jungle creature die in order for the jungle timer to register which makes it 100% pointless in regards to gaining an advantage over the enemy team. So all in all, my question is should I completely remove my use of mkJogo (which I only use for the &quot;offline&quot; skins) or should I ignore the email?
Write Your Thoughts
